# Bastion policy and its workflow are owned paths: editing a reviewer, loosening
# a trigger, or changing the review job requires a maintainer review, so the merge
# gate cannot be weakened or switched off without a human in the loop. CODEOWNERS
# itself is owned for the same reason. (CODEOWNERS changes only take effect once
# merged, so these patterns must statically cover every path Bastion governs.)
/.bastion.yaml                  @jssblck
/.github/workflows/bastion.yml  @jssblck
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @jssblck
